Barrière</b> (see   Barriere  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Street","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>stret(e)</i> ‘street, Roman road’ (Old English <i>strǣt</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived in the main street of a village or town or by a Roman road, or habitational, from a place so named, such as Street (Kent, Herefordshire, Somerset), Street on the Fosse (Somerset), Strete in Blackawton (Devon), Strete Raleigh in Whimple (Devon), or Streat (Sussex). In the Middle Ages the word at first denoted a Roman road but later also came to denote the main street in a town or village.","Americanized form (translation into English) of Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Strasser   and a number of other surnames with similar meaning.","Americanized form of Jewish (from Morocco) <b>Chetrit</b>: perhaps from the Arabic verbal root <i>shṭr</i> ‘to become skillful, dexterous, astute’. The exact origin of the suffix <i>–it</i> is unclear."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Gates was born in 1140, in England, United Kingdom, his father, William Gates 1st, was 26 and his mother, Mrs. William Gates 1st, was 25. He married Mrs. William Gates before 1180. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"1140–":"1140–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1114–Male":"1114–Surnud","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","before1180":"enne 1180","1115":"1115","1114":"1114","1140":"1140","1180":"1180","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1140–":"1140–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1114–Male":"1114–Kuollut","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","before1180":"ennen vuotta 1180","1115":"1115","1114":"1114","1140":"1140","1180":"1180","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1140–":"1140–Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1140–Female":"1140–Décédée","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1114–Male":"1114–Décédé","1115–Female":"1115–Décédée","before1180":"avant 1180","1115":"1115","1114":"1114","1140":"1140","1180":"1180","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Gates est né en 1140, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, William Gates 1st, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Mrs. William Gates 1st, avait 25 ans. Il a épousé Mrs. William Gates avant 1180. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1140–":"1140–Verstorben","1140–Male":"1140–Verstorben","1140–Female":"1140–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","1114–Male":"1114–Verstorben","1115–Female":"1115–Verstorben","before1180":"vor 1180","1115":"1115","1114":"1114","1140":"1140","1180":"1180","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als William Gates 1140 in England, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war sein Vater William Gates 1st 26 und seine Mutter Mrs. William Gates 1st 25. Er hat vor 1180 Mrs. William Gates geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1140–":"1140–Desede","1140–Male":"1140–Desede","1140–Female":"1140–Desede","1180–Male":"1180–Desede","1114–Male":"1114–Desede","1115–Female":"1115–Desede","before1180":"before 1180","1115":"1115","